<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406791>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Lithopanopeus truesdalei n. gen., n. sp., male holotype (USNM 1611097 = ULLZ 17919) A–F, H; male paratype (USNM 1541468 = ULLZ 6447) G, I. A, right side of carapace, dorsal surface; B, left side of carapace, ventral surface; C, right third maxilliped detached, external surface, (arthrobranch gill pair not shown); D, right third maxilliped detached, internal surface; E., major (left) cheliped, supero-internal surface; F, major (left) chela, external surface; G, major (left) chela fingers, external surface; H, minor (right) cheliped, infero-external surface; I, minor (right) cheliped, supero-internal surface. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4406791/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406797>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Lithopanopeus truesdalei n. gen., n. sp., female paratype (USNM 1611099 = ULLZ 18401). A, right side of carapace, dorsal surface (setae not shown); B, major (right) cheliped, supero-internal surface; C, thoracic sternum, pleon lifted away to expose gonopores; D, pleon, external surface. Scale bars = 2.0 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4406797/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406801>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Lithopanopeus truesdalei n. gen., n. sp. A, male holotype (USNM 1611097 = ULLZ 17919) cw 9.6 mm, northwestern Gulf of Mexico; B, juvenile male paratype (USNM 1541468 = ULLZ 6447) cw 6.3 mm, southwestern Gulf of Mexico." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4406801/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4406795>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Lithopanopeus truesdalei n. gen., n. sp., male holotype (USNM 1611097 = ULLZ 17919) A–C, E–I; male paratype (USNM 1541468 = ULLZ 6447) D, J. A, right second pereopod, upper surface; B, right third pereopod, lower surface; C, right fourth pereopod, upper surface; D, right fifth pereopod, upper surface; E, pleon, sternum, and pereopod coxae, posteroventral surfaces; F, pleon disarticulated; G, right first gonopod, lateral surface; H, right first gonopod, sternal surface; I, right first gonopod, abdomino-mesial surface; J, right second gonopod, pleonal surface. Scale bar = 3.0 mm (A–C); 2.0 mm (D–F); 1.0 mm (G, J); 0.5 mm (H, I)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4406795/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

